  "inscription": "<br />1866-1935  <br />William Wallace Atterbury  <br />Tenth President of The Pennsylvania Railroad  <br />Director General of Transportation of  American Expeditionary Forces - World War I.  <br />Friend of Labor - Pioneer in collective bargaining  <br />Servant of the American people in war and peace  <br />With courage and foresight he introduced  electrification in to the railroad's system  <br />1861 - 1940  <br />George Gibbs  <br />Consulting Engineer  <br />Whose vision and tenacity of purpose  led to the development of the  <br />Pennsylvania Railroad's articulated  electric locomotive class GG1  <br />placed in operation 1934  <br />and contributed so much to the  advancement of the art of electric railroad  transportation  <br />1808 - 1874  <br />J. Edgar Thomson  <br />Father of the Pennsylvania Railroad  <br />First Chief Engineer - Third President  <br />He planned the railroad's present system  <br />He left his fortune in trust for  the education and maintenance of female orphans  of railway employees whose fathers may have  been killed in the discharge of their duties",
  "architecture": {
    "description": "North Waiting Room"
  },
